{"word":"ἀζαλέος","slug":"ἀζαλέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀζαλέος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><el>ἄζω</el>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>dry, parched</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>βῶν ἀζαλέην</el> the <i>dry</i> bull's-hide, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>dry, harsh</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>parching, scorching</i>, <el>Σείριος</el> <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}